# Testing

Run the **smallest scope that catches your regression** after substantive edits. Full gate: `mvn verify` once before marking done — see [issues-quality.mdc](issues-quality.mdc).

**Session end:** never stop with failing tests in your diff — run at least the affected test class, then `mvn verify` before handing off ([development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) § Working code invariant).

## Tiered ladder

| When | Command |
|------|---------|
| Trivial / compile-only edit | Skip until next substantive change |
| One backend package edited | Single test class or `mvn test -Dtest=ClassName` |
| REST endpoint changed | Related `*EndpointTest` + `ArchitectureTest` if DTOs changed |
| Angular component/service changed | `cd src/main/webui && npm run build` then `npm test -- --include='**/affected.spec.ts'` |
| Task done (backend) | `mvn verify` |
| Task done (full-stack) | `mvn verify` + `npm run build` + Angular tests (CI runs both) |

```bash
# All backend tests
mvn test

# Single test
mvn test -Dtest=TicketEndpointTest#methodName

# Architecture rules
mvn test -Dtest=ArchitectureTest

# Frontend (headless)
cd src/main/webui && npm run build
cd src/main/webui && npm test -- --no-watch --browsers=ChromeHeadless

# Dev mode (manual)
mvn quarkus:dev
```

## Impact map

| You changed | Run |
|-------------|-----|
| `ticket/*` | `TicketEndpointTest`, `TicketHistoryServiceTest` |
| `auth/*`, `user/*` | `AuthenticationEndpointTest`, `UserEndpointTest` |
| `project/*` | `ProjectEndpointTest` |
| `workflow/*` | `WorkflowEndpointTest` |
| `*Request`/`*Response` records | `ArchitectureTest` + affected endpoint tests |
| Angular service | Matching `*.service.spec.ts` |
| Angular component | Matching `*.component.spec.ts` |

Detail: [issues-tests.mdc](issues-tests.mdc).

TDD development guidance: [issues-model.mdc](issues-model.mdc) § TDD.

## When tests fail

1. Re-run smallest repro — [issues-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc](issues-test-failure-diagnosis.mdc).
2. Do not loop full `mvn verify` per fix.
3. After green: one report under `reports/` per that rule.

## Infra to reuse

- `Given` builder in `src/test/java/dev/vepo/issues/Given.java` for seed users, projects, tickets.
- REST Assured with `@QuarkusTest` — not ad-hoc HTTP clients in tests.
- No `Thread.sleep()` — use Awaitility if async timing is needed.
